Spatz,<br><br>
You know, you are incredible. No, let me change that to sanctimonious!  But in a bullshit sort of way.<br><br>
You have always been in the thick of things when it comes to namecalling! <br><br>
Is my reference to the lie you told &quot;namecalling&quot;? Where have I called you a name? You told a lie about lying down in front of a train in order to lend yourself credibility. You can't weasel out of it, spatz. Does this make me partial? Yes, of course it does! I'm partial to the truth.<br><br>
Cook Barela and I differ on many things. These things are documented on this website. I stand by everything I said and I am certain that he stands by his opinions, also. There is absolutely no reason for either one of us to change our stance on anything. Having said that, let me say that there is no reason, whatsoever, for us to tear each other to shreds - unless it is for the amusement of one Barry Spatz.<br><br>
The various viewpoints held by the veterans on this site are just that! Various. Different. Divergent. When we, as veterans, are able to look past viewpoints which are vastly different from ours and still are able to embrace each other as people, this is called HEALING. <br><br>
Acceptance and recognition were commodoties in short supply when we came home. It is evident how precious they are today. Acceptance and recognition mean the most when they are received from our peers. Call it what you will, but a pat on the back or a kind word mean the most when they are spoken between vets. Don't bother yourself trying to understand all that you term &quot;mumbo jumbo&quot;. We vets do understand. People who are shunned are forced to adopt a pack mentality. We understand that also.<br><br>
It is not for me to include or exclude anyone. As has been mentioned, this is a free site. I encourage all vets to participate.<br><br>

